{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01TLrzcvsAtH2Pp8mfqLAQbd","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01QT8htTrAEjwhHFn2Xrm1iU","name":"Agent","input":{"description":"Check staging services and logs","prompt":"You are a fix-checker agent. Check staging services and recent autonomous dev logs.\n\n1. Check PM2 processes on the VM:\n```bash\nssh REDACTED_VM_HOST \"pm2 jlist\" 2>/dev/null\n```\nLook for processes with status !== \"online\" or high restart counts (>10). Report any staging processes that are down.\n\n2. Read the autonomous dev progress log:\n```bash\ncat REDACTED_REPOS_ROOT/auto-dev/logs/progress.md | tail -100\n```\nLook for any FAIL entries or incomplete sessions.\n\n3. Read the fix-checker failure log:\n```bash\ncat REDACTED_REPOS_ROOT/auto-dev/fix-checker/logs/failures.md | tail -50\n```\nLook for recurring patterns.\n\nReport what you find. If everything looks healthy, say \"all clear\".","subagent_type":"general-purpose","name":"staging-checker","mode":"bypassPermissions"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4523,"cache_read_input_tokens":14113,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":4523},"output_tokens":9,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f64a6d3f-4690-4a87-aa5b-66418f809ed2","uuid":"55353fd6-af99-45e5-8f90-a07e0e1a48f4"}
