{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_012rigJyqVe569NqhDkHSyQ6","type":"tool_result","content":"- Added standalone ESLint flat config (`eslint.config.mjs`) with:\n  - TypeScript support via `typescript-eslint`\n  - React hooks plugin (`eslint-plugin-react-hooks`)\n  - Next.js plugin (`@next/eslint-plugin-next`)\n  - Node.js globals for server-side files (lib/, api/, middleware)\n  - Extension directory excluded (browser JS with chrome/document globals)\n- Fixed 2 lint errors surfaced by the new config:\n  - `src/app/my-prompts/page.tsx`: `<a>` tag → `<Link>` from `next/link` (no-html-link-for-pages)\n  - `src/lib/sanitize.ts`: removed unnecessary regex escape `\\/` → `/` in bearer token pattern\n- Added `npm run lint` script to package.json\n- Added lint step to CI workflow (runs before type check)\n- Result: 0 errors, 5 warnings (all expected no-img-element for external OAuth avatar URLs)\n- 66 tests passing, build clean\n- Deployed to staging — app running (302 redirect to auth)\n\n### Survey findings (for future sessions)\n- **promptlibrary**: Now has linting. Remaining opportunities: component-level React tests (would need jsdom), skip-to-content link, heading hierarchy audit\n- **social-tools**: Still missing ESLint setup — good candidate for next session\n- **All repos**: Clean audit (except known unfixable transitive deps), tests passing, CI active, branches clean\n\n---\n\n## 2026-03-20 — Run 43\n\n### What was done\n\n**social-tools — ESLint configuration with TypeScript and React hooks rules (PR #43, auto-merged)**\n- Added standalone ESLint flat config (`eslint.config.mjs`) with:\n  - TypeScript support via `typescript-eslint`\n  - React hooks plugin (`eslint-plugin-react-hooks`)\n  - Node.js globals for server-side files\n  - PM2 ecosystem config excluded\n- Fixed 9 lint errors surfaced by the new config:\n  - Removed 6 unused imports: `StarRating` (CategoryPage), `FeedResponse`/`Category` (CirclePage), `Users` (HomePage), `eq` (seed.ts), `beforeAll` (routes.test.ts)\n  - Replaced unsafe `Function` type with explicit `(...args: unknown[]) => void` in test helper\n  - Fixed `setState`-in-effect pattern in `useApi` hook (guarded with mounted ref)\n- Added `npm run lint` script to package.json\n- Added lint step to CI workflow (runs before type check)\n- Result: 0 errors, 0 warnings, 136 tests passing, build clean\n\n### Survey findings (for future sessions)\n- **social-tools**: Now has linting. All Tier 1-3 features complete, 136 tests, CI with lint/check/test/build/smoke.\n- **groceryGenius**: Missing standalone ESLint setup (currently uses `next lint` which may break on Next.js upgrades like runeval did)\n- **All repos**: Clean audit (except known unfixable transitive deps), tests passing, CI active, branches clean\n\n---\n\n## 2026-03-20 — Run 44\n\n### What was done\n\n**social-tools — Comprehensive WCAG accessibility pass (PRs #44-#45, auto-merged)**\n- **Card component**: Added keyboard support (Enter/Space to activate) with focus ring for all clickable cards across the app\n- **ReactionButtons**: Added `aria-pressed` toggle state and `aria-label` with counts on both helpful/agree buttons\n- **SortPills**: Added `aria-pressed` on active pill, `role=\"group\"` with label on container\n- **StarRating**: Added `role=\"img\"` with descriptive `aria-label` (\"Rating: X.X out of 5 stars\")\n- **TrustBadges**: Added `aria-label` on badges, `aria-hidden` on decorative icons\n- **Header**: `aria-label` on nav, search form `role=\"search\"`, `sr-only` label for search input, `aria-current=\"page\"` on active nav link, `aria-label` on all nav links (for mobile icon-only view)\n- **App.tsx**: Wrapped page content in `<main>` landmark\n- **ReviewerSelector (ComparePage)**: Added `aria-haspopup=\"listbox\"`, `aria-expanded`, `role=\"listbox\"`/`role=\"option\"`, Escape key to close\n- **All back buttons** (4 pages): Added `aria-label`\n- **All search inputs** (3 locations): Associated `<label>` elements via `htmlFor`/`id`\n- **All filter pill groups** (3 pages): `role=\"group\"` with `aria-label`, `aria-pressed` on each pill\n- **40+ decorative Lucide icons**: Marked `aria-hidden=\"true\"` across 14 files\n- **Non-semantic interactive elements**: Replaced clickable `<span>`s with `<button>`s in ReviewCard and CirclePage FeedCard; wrapped clickable `<h2>` content in `<button>` on ComparePage\n- **Pagination (CategoryPage)**: Wrapped in `<nav aria-label=\"Pagination\">`, added `aria-label` on prev/next buttons\n- **Follow button (PersonPage)**: Added `aria-pressed` toggle state\n- **Load more button (CirclePage)**: Added `aria-busy` during loading\n- Result: 0 lint errors, 0 type errors, 136 tests passing, build clean\n\n### Survey findings (for future sessions)\n- **social-tools**: Now fully accessible. All Tier 1-3 features complete, 136 tests, CI with lint/check/test/build/smoke.\n- **groceryGenius**: Already has standalone ESLint (Vite project, not Next.js — previous note was incorrect). Already had WCAG pass (Run 40).\n- **promptlibrary**: Already had WCAG pass (Run 41) and ESLint (Run 42).\n- **Remaining a11y opportunities**: runeval (main product, no a11y pass yet), valueSortify, pezantTools\n- **All repos**: Clean audit (except known unfixable transitive deps), tests passing, CI active, branches clean\n\n---\n\n## 2026-03-20 — Run 45\n\n### What was done\n\n**runeval — Comprehensive WCAG accessibility pass (PRs #42-#44, auto-merged)**\n- **Layout**: Added skip-to-content link, `aria-label=\"Main navigation\"` on nav, single `<main id=\"main-content\">` landmark in root layout, replaced nested `<main>` tags with `<div>` across 16 page files, `aria-hidden` on decorative nav separator\n- **DashboardClient**: `role=\"group\"` with `aria-label=\"Activity filter\"` on filter pills, `aria-pressed` on each pill, `aria-busy` on sync button, `role=\"alert\"` on sync error, `aria-label=\"Dismiss notification\"` on dismiss button, `aria-hidden` on decorative spinner and green status dot\n- **HealthDashboard**: `role=\"group\"` with `aria-label=\"Date range\"` on range pills, `aria-pressed` on each pill, `aria-expanded` and `aria-label` on all metric summary cards (both primary and overflow), `aria-hidden` on emoji icons and green dots, `aria-label` on close button, `role=\"img\"` with descriptive label on SparklineChart\n- **ActivityReportClient**: `aria-label=\"Compare with another activity\"` on select, `aria-busy` on AI report generation button, `role=\"status\"` on email confirmation\n- **StreamChart**: `role=\"img\"` with descriptive `aria-label` (includes min/avg/max stats) on SVG element\n- **ZoneBars**: `role=\"img\"` with zone distribution `aria-label`, `aria-hidden` on visual bar elements\n- **Imports page**: `role=\"button\"` + `tabIndex` + keyboard support (Enter/Space) on expandable job rows, `aria-expanded` on expandable rows, `aria-label` on delete buttons, `role=\"alert\"` on upload errors, `role=\"status\"` on success messages, `aria-hidden` on arrow indicators\n- **Auth pages** (login, register, forgot-password, reset-password): `role=\"alert\"` on all error messages, `role=\"status\"` on success messages, `aria-hidden` on Google OAuth SVG\n- **Settings page**: `role=\"status\"` on save feedback, `aria-hidden` on green connection dot\n- Result: 0 lint errors, 0 type errors, 129 tests passing, build clean\n- Deployed to staging — 308 (auth redirect, app running correctly)\n\n### Survey findings (for future sessions)\n- **runeval**: Now has WCAG accessibility pass. All major repos now accessible (groceryGenius Run 40, promptlibrary Run 41, social-tools Run 44, runeval Run 45)\n- **Remaining a11y opportunities**: valueSortify, pezantTools (lower priority — simpler apps)\n- **All repos**: Clean audit, tests passing, CI active, branches clean","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01QT8htTrAEjwhHFn2Xrm1iU","session_id":"f64a6d3f-4690-4a87-aa5b-66418f809ed2","uuid":"afb0312b-b1ba-4c22-83d5-14203d